HEADWORD: Proclive
<hw>Pro*clive"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>proclivis</ets> sloping, inclined; <ets>pro</ets> forward +
<ets>clivus</ets> hill: cf. F. <ets>proclive</ets>. See
<er>Declivity</er>, and cf. <er>Proclivous</er>.]</ety> <def>Having a
tendency by nature; prone; proclivous.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Mrs. Browning.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
